task.summary: Email verification is no longer crashing!! Button on signed in as player is a placeholder.
idk how but I got some geofence stuff to work. The app will think that the current location is near Google HQ. This is only because it is being emulated.

fixed the notifications not working, tried fiddlding with buttons to get yes/no to work when in fenced location, app would keep crashing, using more elegant solution, when user is in fenced are just take them to the page instead of asking
quickfix, put the wrong intents on the wrong activities

Changed string on first button that shot you to the game activity to "anon sign in", added primitive group feature that uses firebase database, checks if user is playing,in the future will remove timer when it is added (only in group is timer removed).

-Created adapter view to see a list of all courses -Allow users to select course -Allow users to filter through courses (Not 100% working) -Allow users to send in game request. -once the request on firebase equals true, the user can start the game -Game schema is created in firebase after the user selects "start game" -added backgrounds and opacity to the PresentatonActivity, SigninActivity, and SignupActivity

Created -Game set up -Start Game -keeping track of which hole the player is on -google map api hole set up. -calculated distance from teeing point to hole. -map zoom in in between the teeing point and hole for which hole the player is on. -added map icons for teeing point and hole.
Keeps track of players score in firebase
New game set up activity, new UI Lets User add and delete from their group. Users will now be starting games as groups.
Debugged GameSetup UI keeps all the game setup info as users switch between activities

New UI for game activity. Uses fragments to switch between the game, game over view, Admin requests and next hole info. Users can now tap within a geofence and it will tell the user how far they are from the hole. Added game info that Danny requested. There is a bug within the fragments right now. When you switch out of the game tab and back to it the app crashes. Its a situation with saving the activity state when you switch out of it. Looking into this.
Fixed issue with it crashing. Still not saving the state when switching between fragments though
Saving activity state by pulling from firebase instead of handling it on the android end
